result.execSummary:
The defendant Kris A Hansen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Cash bond on file shall be applied to amounts due. If bond has been refunded, amounts due can be taken from prison wages and paid while on extended supervision. If extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.
Defendant shall not possess firearms or weapons.

Defendant shall not have direct or indirect contact with MRR or his family or residence(s). 
Defendant shall not have direct or indirect contact with anyone under age 18 except as authorized by his supervising agent.
Defendant shall not enter any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale or service of alcohol.

Defendant shall participate in sex offender treatment and all counseling or treatment programs as directed by his supervising agent. 
Defendant shall provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Defendant has the right to request expungement of DNA analysis in writing through the Department of Justice.
Defendant shall comply with sex offender registration.
Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.
Defendant shall pay Dept of Corrections supervision fees.
